1624 |     +                     CUM_CONTRACT_CAP,|
1625 |     +                     REMAINING_ENRG_ONLY_ENRG,|
1626 |     +                     TOTAL_CONTRACT_ENRG,ISEAS)|
1627 |!|
1628 |!     CONTRACTS PROVIDES AN ABILITY TO INCORPORATE PURCHASE POWER|
1629 |! CONTRACTS INTO THE PRODUCTION COSTING OF CL UNITS.|
1630 |!|
1631 |!     SUBROUTINE CONTRACTS IS CALLED BY DR_BOOTH INSIDE THE UNITS|
1632 |! COUNTER.  IF A UNIT SEGMENT IS NOT MUST RUN, AND THE|
1633 |! CL_DISPATCH_COST IS GREATER THAN THE LOWEST AVAILABLE|
1634 |! CONTRACT_DISPATCH_COST, AND THE CONTRACTS OPTION IS ACTIVE,|
1635 |! THE CONTRACTS SUBROUTINE IS CALLED.|
1636 |!|
1637 |!     CONTRACTS HAVE THE FOLLOWING CHARACTERISTICS:|
1638 |!|
1639 |!     ENERGY_COST|
1640 |!     CAPACITY_COST (VARIES WITH THE MAXIMUM CONTRACTED CAPACITY)|
1641 |!     FIXED_CAPACITY_COST (CAN BE DIFFERENT THAN CAPACITY COST)|
1642 |!     MINIMUM_ENERGY (CONSTRAINT)|
1643 |!     MAXIMUM_ENERGY (CONSTRAINT)|
1644 |!     MINIMUM_CAPACITY (CONSTRAINT)|
1645 |!     MAXIMUM_CAPACITY (CONSTRAINT)|
1646 |!     CONTRACT_ENERGY (STATE VARIABLE)|
1647 |!     CONTRACT_CAPACITY (STATE VARIABLE)|
1648 |!     AVAILABLE_CONTRACT (STATE VARIABLE)|
1649 |!|
1650 |! NOTES ON INTERFACE WITH MIDAS:|
1651 |!|
1652 |!     THE PARAMETERS THAT MIDAS AND THE CONTRACTS MODEL PASS BACK|
1653 |!     AND FOURTH ARE: PRODUCTION DISPATCH AND CONVOLVING INFO,|
1654 |!     COST INFORMATION.|
1655 |!     PRODUCTION DISPATCH PARAMETERS ARE: A,RIGHT,LODDUR,LPROB,|
1656 |!     CL_DISPATCH_COST AND REMAINING_ENERGY|
1657 |!     SUBROUTINE ASSUMES UNITS ARE LOADED INSIDE|
1658 |!     THE UNITS COUNTER, AFTER MAINTENANCE CALC AND BEFORE ANY ENER|
1659 |!     ALLOCATION.  THE ALGORITHM TAKES THE CURRENT RIGHT ELDC|
1660 |!     BOUNDARY AND LOADS CONTRACTS UNDER THE ELDC UNTIL A STOPPING|
1661 |!     CONDITION IS REACHED.  THEN, THE RIGHT BOUNDARY, REMAINING_|
1662 |!     ENERGY, AND CL_DISPATCH_COST ARE CHANGED TO REFLECT|
1663 |!     CONTRACTS.  SUBROUTINE ASSUMES A IS THE NEW LEFT BOUNDARY.|
