i:  3731  |C THE number of values is returned and ignored (should be a subroutine).| 
i:  3732  |C The new value(s) are set in R_VALUE_ARRAY directly.| 
i:  3733  |C| 
i:  3734  |         ! It doesn't matter what is returned from this routine. It| 
i:  3735  |         ! returns a value because it's an `ENTRY` and not a separate| 
i:  3736  |         ! subroutine. Return value is meaningless and ignored everywhere| 
i:  3737  |         ! it is encountered.| 
i:  3738  |         ESCALATE_ALL_VALUES = -1  | 
i:  3739  || 
i:  3740  |         DO I = 1, NUM_VALS| 
i:  3741  |            POSITION_IN_VECTOR_MAP = R_VECTOR_NO_ARRAY(I)| 
i:  3742  |            IF(POSITION_IN_VECTOR_MAP < -1 .OR. | 
i:  3743  |     +         POSITION_IN_VECTOR_MAP > MAXIMUM_VECTOR_NUM) | 
i:  3744  |     +            CALL BAD_ESC_VECTOR_NUMBER(| 
i:  3745  |     +             POSITION_IN_VECTOR_MAP,MAXIMUM_VECTOR_NUM,| 
i:  3746  |     +                                                   RECORD_NAME(I))| 
i:  3747  |            I4 = I4_VECTOR_MAP(POSITION_IN_VECTOR_MAP)| 
i:  3748  |            IF(VECTOR_TYPE_IS_VALUE(I4)) THEN| 
