i:  8124  |! ROUTINE:          **** C O N V O L ****| 
i:  8125  |!| 
i:  8126  |! PURPOSE:| 
i:  8127  |!    TO CONVOLVE THE EQUIVALENT LOAD DURATION CURVE| 
i:  8128  |!| 
i:  8129  |!  INPUT VARIABLES| 
i:  8130  |!    CAPON    THE AMOUNT OF CAPACITY TO BE CONVOLVED| 
i:  8131  |!    P        THE AVAILABILITY OF THE UNIT| 
i:  8132  |!    CURRENT  THE POINT SHOWING THE POSITION OF THE INCOMING LPROB| 
i:  8133  |!    DELTA    THE CALCULATION GRID SPACING| 
i:  8134  |!    LPROB    THE LPROBS| 
i:  8135  |!| 
i:  8136  |!  OUTPUT VARIABLES| 
i:  8137  |!    LPROB    THE NEW LPROB| 
i:  8138  |!  INTERNAL VARIABLES| 
i:  8139  |!    ITEMP    TEMPORARY INTEGER STORAGE LOCATION| 
i:  8140  |!    SHIFT    THE NUMBER OF INDEX POSITIONS THE LPROB IS SHIFTED| 
i:  8141  |!    INDEX    THE LAST GRID POSITION FOR CALCULATION| 
i:  8142  |!    Q        THE UNAVAILABILITY OF THE UNIT| 
i:  8143  |!  ALGORITHM| 
i:  8144  |!    SAME AS PCS MODEL.  BASED ON THE BOOTH - BALERIAUX METHOD| 
i:  8145  |!    SPECIALIZED FOR MIDAS| 
i:  8146  |!| 
i:  8147  |!  AUTHOR:| 
i:  8148  |!    M. S. GERBER & ASSOCIATES, INC.| 
